name: Starbucks
directions: When you walk in, the two bathrooms are immediately on your right down the small hallway.
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer! As a barista who works here, our bathrooms are open to everyone. There's no key-code needed to enter, either (some Starbucks locations have a passcode to get into the bathroom; we do not). The bathrooms are single-rooms, with large doors. There are no stalls or shared bathrooms, they are entirely private.

comment: Ideally for paying customers

name: Starbucks

name: Broken Arrow Warren Theatre
directions: (Note: As far as I know, there are none available unless you buy a ticket) Through the front entrance just keep on walking straight. After you give your ticket to the employee, take a left and there is a single-use unisex restroom right on the left-wall.
comment:
As noted, it is past the point where tickets are taken. It makes Warren Theatre a GREAT theater to choose, as I don't know of any others around that have a unisex restroom.

(I have only been once, and it's possible - perhaps even probable - that's there might be another unisex restroom or two in the theater)
